Lipsiæ, 1752, 4o, 34 pp.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p76"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p76.1"></span>Döllinger, J. v</span>. *Die Papst-Fabeln
des Mittelalters*. 1863. Cf. Civiltà cattol., ser. 5, v. 10 (1864),
303–330; tr. Ger. Mainz, 1867. gr. 8o, 34 pp.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p77"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p77.1"></span>Döllinger</span>. In Münchener Hist.
Jahrb. (1865), 337–.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p78"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p78.1"></span>Dudley, Dean</span>. *History of the
First Council of Nice: A world’s Christian convention, A.D. 325; with a
life of Constantine*. Boston, Dean Dudley & Co., 1879, 120 pp.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p79"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p79.1"></span>Duerr, Joan Frid</span>. *Dissertatio
