<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p80"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p80.1"></span>Du Pin</span>. *Nov. Bibl. Aut. Eccl*. 2,
p. 16–.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p81"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p81.1"></span>Duruy, Vict</span>. *Les premières années
du règne de Constantin* (305–323). In Compte rendu acad. scien. mor.
polit. (1881). F. XVI. 737–765. Speaks of his “cold cruelty.” He was
convinced that “the future was victory to Christians, and political
wisdom counselled to go with them.”

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p82"></span>—— —— *La politique religieuse de
Constantin* (312–337). In Compte rendu acad. scien. mor. polit. (1882),
XVII. 185–227. Orleans, 1882, 8o, 47 pp. = Rev. archæolog., 1882, B.
XLIII. 96–110, pl. 155–175. Cf. Allard, P., in Lettres chrét. (1882), V.
244–249. “Fragment de son Histoire des Romains.” Treats: I. La vision
miraculeuse. II. Le lavarum. III. Popularité croissante du culte du
Soleil. IV. Constantin à Rome en 312: son arc de triomphe. V. L’édit de
Milan (313). VI. Mesures pour l’éxecution de l’édit de Milan. VIII.
Monnaies de Constantin; Constantinople. IX. Resumé.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p83"></span>—— —— *Les conditions sociales au
temps de Constantin*. In Compte rendu acad. scien. mor. polit. (1882),
XVIII. 729–772. Treats: La cour, La noblesse, La bourgeoisie, La plèbe,
Les corporations réglementées, L’armée.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p84"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p84.1"></span>Du Voisin, J. B</span>. *Dissertation
critique sur la vision de Constantin*. Paris, 1774. 12o, 331 pp. Cf.
Journ. d. sçavans (1774), 452–459.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p85"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p85.1"></span>Eckhel</span>. *Doctrina numorum
veterum*. 8 (Vindob. 1828), 71–95.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p86"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p86.1"></span>Eltz, H</span>. In Public. hist. Inst.
Luxembourg (1874–1875), XXIX. 225–236. In this paper, p. 215–236, p.
225–235, are occupied with coins of Constantine and his sons.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p87"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p87.1"></span>Ewyck, Florentius ob</span>. *Oratio in
laudem Constantini Magni habitu a…Tempore Exanimis Huberni Gandæ a. d.
XII. Cal. Januar. MDCXCIII*. Gandæ, 1692, pp. 11 (1). Draws nice little
moral of the “good example” from Constantine.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p88"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p88.1"></span>Fabricius, Joan. Alb</span>. *Dissertatio
de cruce Constantini Magni qua probatur eam fuisse phænomenon in halone
solari, quo Deus usus, sit ad Constantini Magni animum promovendum*.
Hamburgi, 1706. 40 (or Woltereck, who is resp.?). Cf. “Bibl. gr. VI.
(1714–1749), 1–29; IX. 68 (2a, IV. 882; VI. 693–718).”

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p89"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p89.1"></span>Farlati</span>. *Illyric. sac*. VIII.
(1819), 25–27.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p90"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p90.1"></span>Fletcher, Jos</span>. *Life of
Constantine the Great*. London, 1852. 12mo.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p91"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p91.1"></span>Freherus</span>. “Diss. Const. Imp.
Numis.” 1600. Evidently = *Const. Imp. Byz. Numism*. cf. above.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p92"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p92.1"></span>Finckius, Casp</span>. *De disput. de
Baptismo*. T.V. p. 313, disp. XIII.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p93"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p93.1"></span>Frick, Joh</span>. *Dissertatio de fide
Constantini Magni haud dubie christiana*. Ulmæ, 1713. 4o. Not Frick (who
is præses), but Miller (?).

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p94"></span><span id="page_459">p. 459</span>
<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-Page_459"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p94.1"></span>Friedrich, J</span>. *Die Konstantinische
Schenkung*. Nördlingen, 1889. 8o. VII. 197 pp. Reviewed in Theol.
Literaturblatt, 1890, Nos. 3–5; in Evang. Kirch-ztng, No. 18 (1889); by
Schultze, in Theol. Litt. Ber. 1889; Liter. Centralblatt, 1889, No. 33;
by Bloch, in Mttlgn. a. d. histor. Litt. (1890), No. 1; by Löwenfeld, in
Deutsche Ltzng. (1890), No. 3.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p95"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p95.1"></span>Frimelius, Joannis</span>. *De
Constantini Magni Religione, Baptismo & rerum sacrarum apparatu*.
Mentioned by Kunardus, in a “Disputationum Catalogus,” p. (8).

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p96"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p96.1"></span>Frommann, E. A</span>. *De codicibus s.
jussu Constantini ab Eusebio curatis*. Coburgi, 1761. 4o.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p97"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p97.1"></span>Frothingham, Arthur</span>. Compare
edition of Jacobus of Sarug.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p98"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p98.1"></span>Fuhrmann, Matthias</span>. *Historia
sacra de baptismo Constantino Max. Augusti*. I. Romæ, 1742; II. Viennæ
in Austria, 1747, 4o, fig.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p99"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p99.1"></span>Garrucci, Raff</span>. *Esame critico e
cronologico della numismatica Costantiniana portante segni di
cristianesimo*. Roma, 1858, 8o, 72 pp.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p100"></span>—— —— In Vetri cimit. crist. Roma
(1884), append. 1858. Croce greca sulle monete di Costantino e sua
famigla, 89, 90, 91. Croce latina sulle…Costantino padre e figlio e di
Costanzo, 95. Vario modo di figuriale ai tempi di Costantino, 103.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p101"></span>—— —— *Verres ornés de figures en
or, trouvés dans les Catacombes Romaines*. 2d ed. 1864. Has at end
discussion of symbols of Constantine. Compare Anal. Jur. Pout. 1873.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p102"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p102.1"></span>Gasparin, Ag. de</span>. *Innocent III.,
le siècle apostolique, Constantin*. Paris, 1873, 12o, p. 75–193.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p103"></span>—— —— *Constantin*. In *Le
christianisme au quatrième siècle*. Genéve, 1858, 8o, p. 1–139. The
question of church and state. The present problem of the churches is to
undo the work of Constantine. Lectures to Y.M.C.A. of Geneva.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p104"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p104.1"></span>Genelin</span>. *Das
Schenkungsversprechen und die Schenkung Pippins*. Wien und Leipzig.
1880.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p105"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p105.1"></span>Gengel, Georg</span>. *De Constantino
Magno, primo Christianorum imperatore, dissertatio*…Calissii, 1726, 8o,
14–89–6 pp.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p106"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p106.1"></span>Gibbon</span>. *Decline and Fall of the
Roman Empire*. Many editions. Furnishes later historians of Constantine
with almost unlimited material for adoring quotation.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p107"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p107.1"></span>Girault, Cl. Xav</span>. *Dissertation
histor. & critique sur le lieu où la croix miraculeuse apparut à
Constantin & à son armée*. In Magas. encyclop. Paris, 1810, 8o.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p108"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p108.1"></span>Görres, Franz</span>. *Die
Verwandtenmorde Constantin’s des Grossen*. In Ztschr. f. wiss. Theol. 30
(1887), 343–377. Reaches, with Hilgenfeld, the rather severe judgment
that, on the whole, the bloodguiltiness of Licinius is less than that of
Constantine. There are also various other interesting reviews or
treatises by Görres.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p109"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p109.1"></span>Graetz, H</span>. *Die Herrschaft des
Christenthums durch Constantin’s Bekehrung*. In Monatsschrift f. gesch.
u. wiss. Judenthum (1887), 416–421.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p110"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p110.1"></span>Grauert, Herm</span>. *Die
Konstantinische Schenkung*. In Görres-Ges. Histor. Jahrb. 1882–84, III.
p. 3–30; IV. (1883), 45–95, 525–617, 674–680; V. 117–120. Reaches result
that it arose not in Rome, but in France, from the cloister of St.
Denis, shortly before or at the same time with the Pseudo-Isidore, and
shortly after 840. (Weiland, p. 142.)

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p111"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p111.1"></span>Gretser</span>. *De sancta cruce*. In
Opera, v. 2. Ratisbonæ, 1734, fol.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p112"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p112.1"></span>Grisar, Hartm</span>. *Die vorgeblichen
Beweise gegen die Christlichkeit Constantins des Grossen*. In Zeitschr.
f. kathol. Theolog. VI. (1882), 585–607. Cf. La Controverse, 1882, III.
693–702.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p113"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p113.1"></span>Grossius, Matth</span>. *Dissertatio de
donatione Constantini Magni*. Lipsiæ, 1620. 4o.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p114"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p114.1"></span>Gualtherius</span>. See Walther.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p115"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p115.1"></span>Guidi, Ign</span>. *Il battesimo di
Costantino imperatore*. In Nuova Antologia, B. XLI. (1883), 41–52.
Starts from Frothingham’s work. Consult for list of authors who repeat
the story. Mentions some who still believe in the fable.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p116"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p116.1"></span>Gusta, Franc</span>. *Vita di Costantino
