Bibliopolam, 1702, 14 pp. Spoken at the same time with Rouille’s
Oration. Cf. Rouille for estimate.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p135"></span>\[<span class="c13"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p135.1"></span>Hug</span>\] *Denkschrift zur
Ehrenrettung Constantin’s des Grossen*. In Zeitschrift Geistlichkeit
Erzbisth. Freiburg, III. Heft. (Freib. 1829.) 1–104. Treats various
charges. The death of Crispus a plot of Fausta for the sake of her
children, she causing it to seem to Constantine that Crispus and his
nephew were plotting against the empire.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p136"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p136.1"></span>Hunckler</span>. *Constantin le Grand et
son règne*. Limoges, 1843 and 1846. 12o. (“1843, 12o; do. 1846, 12o.”)

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p137"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p137.1"></span>Hynitzsch, Adolf</span>. *Die Taufe
Constantins des Grossen nach Geschichte und Sage*. 1870. Progr. des
Gymnasium in Stendel.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p138"></span>*Incerti auctoris de Constantino
Magno ejusque matre Helena libellus. E codicibus primus edidit*
Eduardus-Heydenreich. Lips., Teubner, 1879. 12o. p. vii. \[1\], 30. See
under *The Mythical Constantine*.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p139"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p139.1"></span>Jacobatius</span>. *De concilio
tractatus*. Romæ, 1538, lib. X. art. 8, p. 780–783. *De donatione
Constantini*.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p140"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p140.1"></span>Jacobus of Sarug</span>. *L’omilia di
Giacomo di Sarúg sul Battesimo di Costantino imperatore*, trad. ed.
annot. da Arthur L. Frothingham, Jr. Roma, 1882. Fol. (From Reale Accad.
dei Lincei. CCLXXIX \[1881–82\].) Consult for various sources and
writers where story is found.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p141"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p141.1"></span>Jacutius, Matth</span>. *Syntagma quo ad
parentis magno Constantino crucis historia complexa est universa*.…Romæ,
1755. 4o.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p142"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p142.1"></span>Janus, Joh. W</span>. *Schediasma
