class="c13"><span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p290.3"></span>Harnack’s</span>
article in Herzog, *Encykl*. on the *Konstantinopolitanisches Symbol*
have a very important correlative bearing, and ought really to be
especially mentioned because the general student would not readily find
them out. Several works on the historical value of Eusebius’ Life of
Constantine, also should really have been inserted. The latest of these
is:

