<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p292"></span>For farther literature on special
points compare references in the notes.

<span id="iv.iii.v.iii-p293"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.iii.v.iii-p293.1"></span>Note 2</span>.—The attempt to secure
accuracy in the above list has proved one of great difficulty. All
references could not be verified, and as “conjectural emendation” is
even more dangerous in bibliography than in textual criticism, readings
have not generally been changed excepting on what seemed actual
evidence. The only way to avoid laying oneself open to criticism in
making a bibliography is not to make it. The editor can only say for
this that a great deal of pains has been expended on improving accuracy
as well as in gathering titles and anotating. The difficulty is shown in
the fact that the work quoted on the double authority of Oettinger and
of Chevalier as by Janus, proves on securing the work itself, after the
list is in plate, to be really by Vogt and dedicated to Janus.

